Previously did not allow for persistent data storage.

Does not fulfill user needs, and has not hit Level-7

This change updates the chatbot to allow for persistent data.

* 'heads/level-7' of https://github.com/emmannyyy/ip:

Previously, all tasks that had dates (i.e: Deadline and Event) were simply using strings to format dates.

Since this would not allow for more functionality for later features, and is also prone to errors, this is suboptimal and should be fixed to allow for date time functionality.

Let's update our product to allow for this functionality, and to hit Level-8

Main class did not make use of Abstraction principles in OOP.

This project has a lot of repeated code, making it inefficient and difficult to maintain.

This update will allow for good abstraction and use of OOP concepts

commitResults.messageBody:
The current code is mostly okay, but still violates some of the standards of the coding quality as specified in the course.

Since we are given more thorough coding standards, the previous coding quality is subpar and must be updated.

Let's update the code to meet the coding standards

The current code does not use assertions, but only does if-else statements for checking of preconditions.

Since we are taught better coding practices involving the assertions, this old method of precondition checking is subpar.

Let's use java assertions to improve code quality and safety.

The current code makes use of for loops instead of streams, which may result in less safe handling of operations.

Since we are taught streams, this use of for loops may provide less safe results as compared to streams.

Let's update the code to use streams instead of for loops, to improve code quality and safety.
Update files to meet code quality

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, the chatbot only handles dates in very specific formats which are not natural to users.

Since we want users to find this chatbot intuitive and user friendly, it would be subpar to not have this feature.

Let's update the Parser class, Event class and Deadline class to allow for usage of more natural dates.
